summary: This is an email chain from September 11, 2019, regarding the booking of travel for an Epstein victim to fly from Palm Beach, Florida, to New York City to meet with the prosecution team (AUSAs and agents) on September 12, 2019. The travel and hotel are to be paid for with USAO funds.

keyFacts: The U.S. Attorney's Office (USAO) approved the use of its funds to pay for an Epstein victim's travel and hotel for an interview.
The victim was to meet with the 'Epstein team of AUSAs and agents' on September 12, 2019, at 5pm in the SDNY.
The email demonstrates active witness coordination and victim support by the prosecution in the Epstein case in September 2019.
All specific personal identifiers for the victim and the email correspondents are redacted in the provided text.
